--------------------------------------------
Fix error at compiling src/slave.c on cygwin
--------------------------------------------
On my fork, I added -I- into AM_CFLAGS after -I.

Note that -I- has been deprecated and we should use -iquote instead of -I:

 http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc/Directory-Options.html

But automake puts -I into DEFAULT_INCLUDES:

 http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/automake/2009-07/msg00006.html

See more detail:

 $ uname -a
 CYGWIN_NT-5.1 jabberwocky 1.7.10(0.259/5/3) 2012-02-05 12:36 i686 Cygwin

 $ ls /usr/include/signal.h
 /usr/include/signal.h

 $ grep -e '#include' /usr/include/poll.h
 #include <sys/poll.h>

 $ grep -e '#include' /usr/include/sys/poll.h
 #include <sys/cdefs.h>
 #include <sys/types.h>
 #include <signal.h>

 $ git clone git://github.com/nickg/nvc.git
 $ cd ~/git-repos/nvc

 $ ls src/rt/signal.h
 src/rt/signal.h

 $ make -k
